Title: Series: Four landscapes with the Holy Family on their Flight into Egypt
Description: The Holy Family near a lake. Landscape with the Virgin holding the swaddled Christ Child as she sits on the ass, Joseph walking behind them at centre right, three cherubs among the three tall trees growing on the mound in left middle distance; from a series of four plates. Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Herman van Swanevelt
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of four, for comment and earlier state see 1844,0425.15.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (6.II)
Acquisition notes: For the history of the acquisition of the Sheepshanks collection, please see Sheepshanks.1
